			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1253844">
									

<p>The way this article looks, I cannot get rid of the feeling its contents belong to the SCP-212 test log or a Foundation tale, not to an independent SCP&#8230; For one thing, it rather strongly references 212. Next, it is almost entirely outdated (which would suggest either having this SCP reclassified as Neutralised or making the remaining nanomachines the SCP). Three, there isn't much going on here! Okay, it was a partially-nanomechanical cyborg which used to collect organic tissue for sustenance until it got trashed. And? I'm almost certain we've got at least one other SCP exhibiting similar properties but much more interesting.</p>
<p>Restating my point for emphasis: in the wider context of SCP-212, Agent AA's story and so on this is pretty good, however IMHO it doesn't hold up to scrutiny as a standalone SCP. Downvoted.</p>

